This is a question that you should ask the College of Engineering: http://engineering.berkeley.edu/student-services/advising/engineering-student-services-advising

My understanding of this page  is that you should have 16B completed before you apply. They may be using your grade in the courses to evaluate your application.

For students attempting to transfer from L&S to COE EECS, I understand that one needs to take both EE16A and EE16B. Does this mean that you have to be taking EE16B at the time you apply, or does it have to be completed before you apply for the major? For an L&S student who is unable to take the class next semester, does that mean that it is impossible to transfer into EECS, as I would be unable to complete EE16A and EE16B before Spring of 2017?
